aamath
------------------------------------------
aamath is a program that reads mathematical expressions in infix notation and
renders them as ASCII art. It may be useful to send mathematics through
text-only media, such as e-mail or newsgroups.

As a simple example, the output for an expression such as

    A_OPR = x*sqrt(x^2-1)/2 - int(sqrt(t^2-1), t = 1 .. x)

will look like


                        x
            ______     /
           / 2        |    ______
       x  / x  - 1    |   / 2
A    = ----------- -  |  / t  - 1 dt
 OPR        2         |
                      |
                     /
                      1


Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-1.7.35-1
  libgcc1-4.9.2-3
  libreadline7-6.3.8-1
  libstdc++6-4.9.2-3

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  binutils-2.25-1
  bison-3.0.4-1
  cygport-0.18.1-1
  gcc-core-4.9.2-3
  gcc-g++-4.9.2-3
  make-4.1-1

Canonical website:
  http://fuse.superglue.se/aamath/

Canonical download:
  http://fuse.superglue.se/aamath/aamath-0.3.tar.gz

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack aamath-0.3-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./aamath-0.3-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/aamath-0.3-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/aamath-0.3-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

(aamath)
  /usr/bin/aamath.exe
  /usr/share/doc/Cygwin/aamath.README
  /usr/share/doc/aamath/COPYING
  /usr/share/doc/aamath/ChangeLog
  /usr/share/doc/aamath/README
  /usr/share/man/man1/aamath.1.gz

